1.	A group is a collection of people who share a common meaning and evaluation of themselves and come together to achieve common goals.
(a) True
(b) False 
Explanation: Kindly refer lecture 17

True. A group is a collection of people who share a common meaning and evaluation of themselves and come together to achieve common goals. This is important for the group to be functional and effective in achieving their objectives.

